      "type": "FACTUAL_FINDING",
      "text": "Mr. Mattingly died on August 5, 2014, five days after a surgical procedure to reverse his colostomy.",
      "paragraph_ref": "19",
      "speaker": "Court finding"
    },
    {
      "evidence_id": "E002",
      "type": "FACTUAL_FINDING",
      "text": "Dr. Anand was involved with Mr. Mattingly\u2019s post-operative care and saw Mr. Mattingly several times while he remained in the medical-surgical unit at WAH.",
      "paragraph_ref": "74",
      "speaker": "Court finding"
    },
    {
      "evidence_id": "E003",
      "type": "EXPERT_TESTIMONY",
      "text": "Dr. Jackson opined that Mr. Mattingly 'died of septic shock' caused by 'an anastomotic leak.'",
      "paragraph_ref": "223",
      "speaker": "Dr. Jackson"
    },
    {
      "evidence_id": "E004",
      "type": "EXPERT_TESTIMONY",
      "text": "The expert testimony of a nursing expert and a surgeon expert, when considered together and in conjunction with other evidence presented at trial, was sufficient to establish the element of causation.",
      "paragraph_ref": "5",
      "speaker": "Court finding"
    },
    {
      "evidence_id": "E005",
      "type": "LEGAL_FINDING",
      "text": "The jury returned a verdict in favor of Ms. Mattingly against both Appellants and awarded damages in the amount of $1,350,000.00.",
      "paragraph_ref": "256",
      "speaker": "Court finding"
    },
    {
      "evidence_id": "E006",
      "type": "COURT_REASONING",
      "text": "The circuit court did not err by submitting the claim premised upon Nurse Matilukuro\u2019s failure to activate the Rapid Response Team to the jury.",
      "paragraph_ref": "499",
      "speaker": "Court finding"
    },
    {
      "evidence_id": "E007",
      "type": "FACTUAL_FINDING",
      "text": "Mr. Mattingly informed nurses overnight that he was in pain. At approximately 5:30 a.m. on August 5, Mr. Mattingly telephoned his mother, Ms. Mattingly.",
      "paragraph_ref": "77",
      "speaker": "Court finding"
    },
    {
      "evidence_id": "E008",
      "type": "EXPERT_TESTIMONY",
      "text": "Nurse Cable testified as to whether Nurse Matilukuro breached the standard of care.",
      "paragraph_ref": "243",
      "speaker": "Nurse Cable"
    },
    {
      "evidence_id": "E009",
      "type": "LEGAL_FINDING",
      "text": "We shall hold that the cremation of Mr. Mattingly\u2019s remains did not constitute spoliation.",
      "paragraph_ref": "55",
